---
description: Invokes before-commit-guard when user runs git commit (pre-commit hook) or fixes a failed commit. Also when editing pre-commit or lint-staged config.
globs: .husky/pre-commit, package.json
alwaysApply: false
---

When any of the following happen, read and follow the **before-commit-guard** skill:

1. **User runs `git commit`** — The Husky pre-commit hook runs **`pnpm guard:pre-commit`**. If the user reports that the commit was rejected or pre-commit failed, invoke the skill to diagnose and fix the failing step (read the **`✗ FAILED at step N/M:`** line).

2. **User asks to fix commit errors / make code commit-ready / fix pre-commit** — Run **`pnpm guard:pre-commit`** (or the failing step only), then fix failures per the skill.

3. **Pre-commit or lint-staged config is modified** — When `.husky/pre-commit`, `src/scripts/tooling/run-pre-commit-guard.ts`, `tooling/ci/run-named-step.sh`, or `package.json` (`guard:pre-commit`, lint-staged) is created or modified, read `agent-os/skills/before-commit-guard/SKILL.md` and ensure the hook steps and this skill stay in sync.

Skill file: `agent-os/skills/before-commit-guard/SKILL.md`
